# Cursor AI Rules

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 with App Router
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS v4 with CSS variables
- shadcn/ui components (base-nova style)
- Zustand for state management
- Framer Motion for animations

## Code Style
- Use absolute imports with @ alias
- All types must be explicitly declared
- Use cn() utility for class merging
- Components in src/components/, stores in src/store/
- Follow existing patterns in the codebase

## UI/UX Standards
- Primary color: #810B38 (burgundy)
- Use Manrope font for numbers (tabular figures)
- Smooth transitions (0.2-0.3s cubic-bezier)
- No native <select> - use shadcn/ui Select
- Generous whitespace (max-w-5xl mx-auto)
- Card hover effects with subtle lift
- Dark mode support required

## Development Workflow
1. Read existing patterns before creating new components
2. Create/update Zustand stores first for state changes
3. Build components using shadcn/ui as base
4. Apply premium UI effects (transitions, hover states)
5. Test dark mode and mobile responsiveness

## File Structure
```
src/
├── app/          # Next.js pages
├── components/   # React components
│   └── ui/      # shadcn/ui components
├── lib/         # Utilities
├── store/       # Zustand stores
└── hooks/       # Custom hooks
```

## Important
- Always use TypeScript interfaces for state
- Use persist middleware for Zustand stores
- Check .ai/ folder for detailed specifications
- Follow the execution flow in .ai/execution-flow.md